Video Title: Making The Burger King Whopper At Home | But Better
Description:
The real king of burgers has arrived. Homemade Buns, perfect patties with that smokey char. This is the ultimate homemade burger. 

Come See Me and Eat My Collab Dish for charity (no there is no event page, just show up and have fun!): Loro Dallas, 1812 N Haskell Ave. https://www.loroeats.com/dallas

Get My Cookbook: http://bit.ly/JWCookbookAmazon

Additional Cookbook Options (other stores, international, etc.): https://bit.ly/TheJWCookbook

Meat Grinder: https://amzn.to/3f3zT8E
KitchenAid Stand Mixer: https://amzn.to/3rFpHIH

FOLLOW ME:
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/joshuaweissman
Tik Tok: https://www.tiktok.com/@flakeysalt
Twitter: https://twitter.com/therealweissman
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/thejoshuaweissman
Subreddit: https://www.reddit.com/r/JoshuaWeissman/
---------------------------------------------------------------

Full Recipe: https://www.joshuaweissman.com/post/making-the-burger-king-whopper-at-home-but-better

Ingredients Needed:

Homemade buns:
1/2 cup (125 ml) whole milk
1/2 cup plus 3 tablespoons (170ml) water
2.5 teaspoons or 9g bread machine yeast
1 egg
1 egg yolk
3.5 cups (525g) bread flour
1/3 cup (60g) granulated sugar
4g amylase
2 teaspoons (7g) fine sea salt (this isn't in the video but it goes in with the flour whoops!)

Dill Pickles
- 1 English cucumber, cut into rounds
- 2 cups (416g) water
- 1.5 cups (306g) vinegar
- 2 tablespoons (19g)kosher salt
- 1 large bunch dill
- 5 cloves garlic
- Sachet of: 1 tablespoon (9g) peppercorns, 1 tablespoon (10g) mustard seeds, 2 tablespoons (8g) coriander seeds, 1 tablespoon (8g) dill seed, 3 bay leaves crumbled_

Mayo:
- 1 egg yolk
- 1 tablespoon (18g) dijon mustard
- 1 clove garlic grated
- 1 teaspoon (5g) sugar
- salt to taste
- juice from 1 whole lemon
- 1 cup or more (191g) vegetable oil

Spicy Ketchup:
- 3/4 cup (215g) ketchup
- 1/2 teaspoon(2g) cayenne powder
- 1 tablespoon (8g) allepo powder
- 1 teaspoon (4g) garlic powder
- 1 teaspooon (5g)Worcestershire sauce


Beef:
- 3/4 lb (340g) boneless chuck roast
- 3/4 lb (340g) boneless short rib 
- 4 slices American cheese (kraft singles)
- 4 slices medium cheddar

Video Title: This Is What Makes Burger King's Whoppers So Delicious
Description:
New menu offerings will always come and go, but one thing that is more or less a permanent fixture on the Burger King menu in the chain's signature burger, The Whopper. First introduced all the way back in 1957, The Whopper was the result of a redesign of how the fast food company cooked burgers. It's been a fan favorite menu item ever since.

Burger King co-founder Jim McLamore explained pretty simply that the name "The Whopper" was chosen to indicate that it was big, and that ended up being true in numerous ways. What explains its enduring popularity and staying power? Here's what makes Burger King's Whoppers so delicious.
